《破碎時光》的第一部在媒體間有著普遍正面的評價，在評分集計網站[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]上獲得了82/100的分數。[[Rev3games|Rev3Games]]的{{link-en|亞當·賽斯勒|Adam Sessler}}給予《破碎時光》4/5分，並將之評為一款美麗並有著優秀且幽默劇本的作品<ref>{{cite web|last=Sessler|first=Adam|title=Broken Age (Part 1) REVIEW! Adam Sessler Reviews|url=http://revision3.com/rev3gamesreviews/broken-age-1-review|work=Rev3Games|publisher=Revision3|accessdate=2014-02-28|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203125922/http://revision3.com/rev3gamesreviews/broken-age-1-review|archivedate=2014-02-03}}</ref>。[[Polygon_(網站)|Polygon]]的賈斯汀·麥克艾洛伊（Justin McElroy）認為《破碎時光》中的角色「平易近人、荒誕又不幸，同時也勇敢並充滿真心誠意」，因此讓遊戲有著「在其他『風趣』遊戲中經常缺少的深度」<ref name=PolyRev1/>。在第一部上市後不到一個月，謝弗表示遊戲銷售的收入已足夠支付第二部的開發費用<ref name=GISales>{{Cite web | url = http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2014-02-21-tim-schafer-how-to-stay-afloat-in-a-pool-of-internet-twitter-hate | title = Schafer: How to stay afloat in "a pool of Internet Twitter hate" | first = Brendan | last = Sinclair | date = 2014-02-21 | accessdate = 2014-02-21 | publisher = Gamesindustry.biz | archive-date = 2014-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140221230953/http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/2014-02-21-tim-schafer-how-to-stay-afloat-in-a-pool-of-internet-twitter-hate | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

=== 影響 ===
對於數百萬美元開發費用的遊戲計劃來說，這項募資活動的成功，讓群眾募資成為在發行商出資（並主控）之外的一項選擇。「[[Rock,_Paper,_Shotgun|Rock, Paper, Shotgun]]」網站的{{link-en|約翰·沃克 (記者)|John Walker (journalist)|約翰·沃克}}指出，雖然這項計劃的成功並未對發行商帶來嚴重威脅，但將能讓發行商開始自我檢討是否與玩者需求脫節<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2012/02/09/thought-double-fines-kickstarter-asks-some-big-questions/ |title=Thought: Double Fine’s Kickstarter Asks Big Questions |publisher=[[Rock,_Paper,_Shotgun|Rock, Paper, Shotgun]] |first=John |last=Walker |date=2012-02-09 |accessdate=2012-02-10 |archive-date=2012-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512090451/http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2012/02/09/thought-double-fines-kickstarter-asks-some-big-questions/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[VG247|VG247]]的強尼·庫侖（Johnny Cullen）將Double Fine的這項募資計劃與[[Radiohead|Radiohead]]的《''[[In_Rainbows|In Rainbows]]''》專輯相比。在實體版本上市前，該專輯便先於官方網站上以「自由樂捐」（pay-what-you-want）的定價方式銷售，而跳過了來自音樂出版商的干預。庫侖並提到曾有遊戲開發者群眾募資失敗的前例，且並不保證在未來複製這項模式便會獲得成功，他認為Double Fine是一間獨特的公司，且有著一群忠實的支持者，而這樣的特質並非其他開發者所擁有<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.vg247.com/2012/02/09/double-fines-kickstart-provides-a-radiohead-moment/ | title = Double Fine’s Kickstarter provides a Radiohead moment | publisher = VG247 | first = Johnny | last = Cullen | date = 2012-02-09 | accessdate = 2012-02-09 | archive-date = 2012-02-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120211041244/http://www.vg247.com/2012/02/09/double-fines-kickstart-provides-a-radiohead-moment/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

《破碎時光》募資的成功，對於冒險類型遊戲產生了特別顯著的影響，也啟發了許多著名的開發者，讓他們開始利用Kickstarter等平台作為重回冒險遊戲開發的第一步<ref name="1UP">{{cite web |url=http://www.1up.com/features/adventure-game-kickstarter-roundup |title=Your Adventure Game Kickstarter Roundup |last=Mackey |first=Bob |date=12 June 2012 |accessdate=28 August 2013 |publisher=[[1UP.com|1UP.com]] |archive-date=2014-01-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116084255/http://www.1up.com/features/adventure-game-kickstarter-roundup |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在「''Double Fine Adventure''」募資成功後的數個月內，包括《{{link-en|斷劍|Broken Sword}}》<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/revolutionsoftware/broken-sword-the-serpents-curse-adventure |title=Broken Sword - the Serpent's Curse Adventure by Revolution Software — Kickstarter |publisher=Kickstarter |accessdate= |archive-date=2014-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714155038/https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/revolutionsoftware/broken-sword-the-serpents-curse-adventure |dead-url=no }}</ref>、《[[狩魔獵人|狩魔獵人]]》<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1005365109/jane-jensens-pinkerton-road-2012-2013-csg |title=Jane Jensen's Moebius and Pinkerton Road Studio by Jane Jensen — Kickstarter |publisher=Kickstarter |accessdate= |archive-date=2012-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120503202538/http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1005365109/jane-jensens-pinkerton-road-2012-2013-csg |dead-url=no }}</ref>、《{{link-en|幻想空間|Leisure Suit Larry}}》<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/leisuresuitlarry/make-leisure-suit-larry-come-again |title=Make Leisure Suit Larry come again! by Replay Games — Kickstarter |publisher=Kickstarter |accessdate= |archive-date=2014-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140722133952/https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/leisuresuitlarry/make-leisure-suit-larry-come-again |dead-url=no }}</ref>、《{{link-en|宇宙傳奇|Space Quest}}》<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/spaceventure/two-guys-spaceventure-by-the-creators-of-space-que |title=Two Guys SpaceVenture - by the creators of Space Quest by Two Guys From Andromeda — Kickstarter |publisher=Kickstarter |accessdate= |archive-date=2014-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140719043021/https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/spaceventure/two-guys-spaceventure-by-the-creators-of-space-que |dead-url=no }}</ref>和《{{link-en|神探墨菲|Tex Murphy}}》等作品的創作者都成功在Kickstarter募得開發所需資金。

